# Agent Rules

## Core Rules

- Preserve YAML frontmatter and keep every concept page with a non-empty `type`.
- Prefer one concept per file where practical.
- Honor `vault_index` and `vault_log` in `gnosis.toml`; update only the enabled navigation artifacts.
- Link sources and references explicitly instead of relying on implicit context.
- Distinguish sourced claims from local decisions or implementation notes.
- Keep generated or derived notes readable as ordinary markdown.
- Do not overwrite unrelated user or agent work; adapt to existing files.
